Key Concepts Explained

Service vs. Pod Communication:

Pods are ephemeral (die/restart frequently), so direct pod-to-pod communication breaks
Services provide stable names/IPs for reliable communication
Deployment vs. StatefulSet:

Deployment: For identical, stateless replicas (e.g., web servers)
StatefulSet: For unique, stateful applications requiring persistent identity (e.g., databases, Netflix subscriptions with different quality tiers)
Persistent Volumes (PV/PVC):

Analogy: Admin uploads movie (PV); user claims it (PVC) and can resume watching later
Volume binds to pod; data persists across pod restarts
Troubleshooting

ImagePullBackOff error: Caused by typos, version mismatches, or network/authorization issues blocking Docker Hub access
Solution: Verify image name/version, check security groups, or use private registries (ECR/GCR) in restricted environments
